FULL TIME POSITION, UK<BR><BR><BR>You will be based in UK and responsible for IN-FUSIO's UK Key Accounts. <BR><BR>Principle duties and responsibilities<BR><BR>·	You will be responsible for obtaining orders that meet or exceed your defined targets <BR>·	You will visit existing clients regularly, and promote and sell the products to potential clients in the most cost effective way, on all levels.<BR>·	All commercial matters will be within your capabilities, i.e. making proposals, negotiating and revising supply group contracts, acting as the principal interface between clients, the clients Marketing Department, Legal Department and Accounts Departments, Handset team.<BR>·	Working closely with the Product Marketing Manager and Sales Project Managers on all Technical matters including the technical response to tenders, technical presentations, compilation of technical documentation and technical support to clients<BR>·	You will be responsible for expanding and developing In-Fusio within the UK based global operators<BR><BR>Education, experience and skills required<BR><BR>·	You already have first experience selling in to the telecom field<BR>·	You have 5+ years experience in the area of Sales and Business Development<BR>·	You speak fluent English<BR>·	You are charismatic and have excellent communication and negotiation skills<BR>·	You must be committed and highly motivated by the challenge of the job as well as successful at managing change and growth<BR><BR>If you are a flexible, proactive individual and you are eager to be a member of a very international sales team (Dutch, Spanish, Italian, French, Iranian, Chinese, American…) and contribute to the further growth of this highly international company (English is the working language), then please send us your CV.<BR><BR>We feel it is very important to help develop the skills of all our employees. <BR>Thus, in order to help you along your career path, we do our <BR>best to maximize the possibility of internal promotion.<BR><BR><BR><BR>
